<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Species characterised by perithecia 1/4-3/4-immersed, leaving usually shallow pits, involucrellum covering half of the exciple or almost to the exciple base, ascospores (23-)25-29(-34) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(10-)11-12(-13) mm, morphologically rather similar to the other Finnish species of the 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, but the sequence divergence in ITS 1.7-2.6%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="holotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Finland, Varsinais-Suomi, Karkkila, Haavisto, 100 m S of E-part of Iitalammi, S-slope, clear cut herb-rich forest, on calcareous stone, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="60" direction="north" minutes="31" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="60.516666">60°31'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="24" direction="east" minutes="23" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="24.383333">24°23'E</geoCoordinate>
